# Masked Loss Implementation — Walkthrough

## What Changed

### New Notebook Cell (inserted after [spl_loss](file:///c:/Users/ANEESHSHASTRI/Documents/GitHub/PRISM/masked_loss.py#171-202) definition)

Contains all masked loss logic — no external [.py](file:///tmp/inspect_masks.py) file needed:

| Component | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| [load_cno_masks()](file:///c:/Users/ANEESHSHASTRI/Documents/GitHub/PRISM/masked_loss.py#47-74) | Loads C/N/O [.filt](file:///c:/Users/ANEESHSHASTRI/Documents/GitHub/PRISM/element%20filters/K.filt) files (7514→8575 gap insertion) |
| [compute_star_pixel_masks()](file:///c:/Users/ANEESHSHASTRI/Documents/GitHub/PRISM/masked_loss.py#80-165) | Per-star pixel masks from [apogee_mask](file:///c:/Users/ANEESHSHASTRI/Documents/GitHub/PRISM/apogee_mask_loader.py#73-109) + CNO filters |
| [masked_spl_loss()](file:///c:/Users/ANEESHSHASTRI/Documents/GitHub/PRISM/masked_loss.py#171-202) | 3-channel `y_true` loss with pixel masking |
| [masked_chi2_estimate()](file:///c:/Users/ANEESHSHASTRI/Documents/GitHub/PRISM/masked_loss.py#204-228) | χ² metric for 3-channel format |
| [GradientGate](file:///c:/Users/ANEESHSHASTRI/Documents/GitHub/PRISM/masked_loss.py#234-260) | Per-sample gradient severing via `tf.stop_gradient` |
| [build_prism_emulator_masked()](file:///c:/Users/ANEESHSHASTRI/Documents/GitHub/PRISM/masked_loss.py#266-390) | PRISM model with gated CNO + abundance inputs |

