## How It Works

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["bad_mask<br/>(N_stars, 23) bool"] --> B["compute_star_pixel_masks"]
    C["apogee_mask.npy<br/>(8575, 27)"] --> B
    D["CNO .filt files<br/>(7514 each)"] --> B
    B --> E["pixel_masks<br/>(N_stars, 8575)"]
    E --> F["TFRecord<br/>spectra = [flux, ivar, pixel_mask]"]
    A --> G["TFRecord<br/>bad_mask = float32 (23,)"]
    
    F --> H{"build_dataset"}
    G --> H
    
    H -->|"dual_input=False"| I["(labels, spectra, weight)<br/>Payne/CNN/EXPayne/RegPayne"]
    H -->|"dual_input=True"| J["((labels, bad_mask), spectra, weight)<br/>PRISM only"]
    
    I --> K["masked_spl_loss<br/>pixel_mask zeros imputed pixels"]
    J --> L["masked_spl_loss + GradientGate<br/>pixel mask + gradient severing"]
```

### GradientGate Math

```python
live = label_value * (1.0 - is_imputed)     # gradient flows
dead = tf.stop_gradient(label_value) * is_imputed  # gradient blocked
return live + dead  # forward pass unchanged for both
```

## Verification Results

20/20 logic checks passed:

- **Notebook structure**: All 14 required functions/configs present
- **Dataset flow**: Single-input models (Payne, CNN, EXPayne, RegPayne) get [(labels, spectra, weight)](file:///c:/Users/ANEESHSHASTRI/Documents/GitHub/PRISM/cnn_label_predictor.py#302-318); PRISM gets [((labels, bad_mask), spectra, weight)](file:///c:/Users/ANEESHSHASTRI/Documents/GitHub/PRISM/cnn_label_predictor.py#302-318)
- **Pixel masks**: C+N overlap test: C=3657, N=3157, overlap=1980, total=4834 ✓
- **Gap insertion**: Blue=3028 + Green=2495 + Red=1991 = 7514 ✓
- **RegPayne**: Uses [masked_spl_loss](file:///c:/Users/ANEESHSHASTRI/Documents/GitHub/PRISM/masked_loss.py#171-202) with single-input dataset ✓

## Computational Cost

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Extra disk (140K stars) | ~4.5 GB |
| Extra GPU memory/batch | ~8.4 MB |
| GradientGate overhead | <1 ms/step |
| Pixel mask multiply | ~0.2 ms/step |
| **Total overhead** | **<5% of ~23 ms/step** |

## Before Running on Kaggle

> [!IMPORTANT]
> 1. **Delete old `.tfrec` files** so `generate_tfrecords()` re-runs with 3-channel spectra
> 2. Adjust `CNO_FILT_DIR` and `APOGEE_MASK_PATH` in Config to match your Kaggle dataset paths
> 3. The backup notebook is at `model-trainer_backup.ipynb`
